  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Protection of SGBV survivors and support to refugees and asylum seekers in Islamabad</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Basic needs support:

- Provision of a subsistence allowance on a monthly basis to the most vulnerable refugees.
- Provision of health care and medical assistance.
- Provision of psychosocial counseling. 
- Provision of educational support (school fees and transportation). 
- Provision of language courses, skill based training and support to access employment.

Safe shelter:

- Medical support
- Psychosocial support
- Interactive learning classes for children
- Legal referral</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Since 2014 ICMC is providing basic needs support to asylum seekers and refugees in Islamabad, including non-Afghan refugees such as Sudanese, Iranian, Iraqis, Palestinians, Somalis, etc. 
Under the same project ICMC runs a safe shelter to assist survivors of Sexual and Gender-Based Violence (SGBV) and their families with their urgent and long-term needs. 
Finally ICMC also conducts Best Interest Determination and Best Interest Assessment for children at risk referred by UNHCR.</narrative>
  </description>
